HEADWORD: Autonomous
<hw>Au*ton"o*mous</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/; <?/
self + <?/ to assign, hold, sway.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Independent in
government; having the right or power of self-government.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Having independent existence or
laws.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Autonomy</ent>⟦br⟧
